The paper is primarily focused on healthcare systems and their challenges, which suggests that it belongs to the cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses a change management framework for healthcare service platforms, which involves the use of Petri nets models. This suggests that the paper could also belong to the cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of modern technologies and telecom capabilities, which could place it in the cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the consistency and correctness of healthcare processes, which could place it in the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) sub-category.
